HEADWORD: Chay root
<hw>Chay" root`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Tamil
<ets>sh⟦amac⟧ya</ets>.]</ety> <def>The root of the <spn>Oldenlandia
umbellata</spn>, native in India, which yields a durable red
dyestuff.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>choy root</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chayote</ent>⟦br⟧
